#: ../../C/chicken-head.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Commodore] The Commodore Business Machines logo, which strongly resembles a"
" poultry part (within Commodore itself the logo was always called chicken "
"lips). Rendered in ASCII as ‘C=’. With the arguable exception of the "
":ref:`Amiga`\\, Commodore's machines were notoriously crocky little "
":ref:`bitty-box`\\es, albeit people have written multitasking Unix-like "
"operating systems with TCP/IP networking for them. Thus, this usage may owe "
"something to Philip K. Dick's novel *Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?* "
"(the basis for the movie *Blade Runner*\\; the novel is now sold under that "
"title), in which a ‘chickenhead’ is a mutant with below-average "
"intelligence."
msgstr ""
"[Commodore] Commodore Business "
"Machinesのロゴで、家禽の部位に強く似ています(Commodore社内ではロゴは常にchicken "
"lipsと呼ばれていました)。ASCIIでは‘C=’と表されます。\\ :ref:`Amiga`\\ "
"という議論の余地のある例外を除けば、Commodoreのマシンは悪名高きクロックな小さな\\ :ref:`bitty-box`\\ "
"でしたが、人々はそれら向けにTCP/IPネットワーキングを備えたマルチタスクのUnix風オペレーティングシステムを書いてきました。したがって、この用法はPhilip"
" K. Dickの小説『Do Androids Dream of Electric "
"Sheep?(アンドロイドは電気羊の夢を見るか?)』(映画『Blade "
"Runner』の原作。小説は今やそのタイトルで売られています)に何か負っているかもしれません。その中で‘chickenhead’は平均以下の知能を持つ変異体です。"
